#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code asteroid collisions ko stack se simulate karta hai.

1. Agar asteroid positive hai, to usse stack me push kar dete hain,
   kyuki wo right direction me ja raha hai.
2. Agar asteroid negative hai, tab collision tabhi hoga
   jab stack top positive ho (matlab saamne se aa raha ho).
3. While loop me chhote positive asteroids ko pop kar dete hain
   agar unka size current negative asteroid se chhota ho.
4. Agar dono same size ke mil gaye, to dono destroy ho jaate hain,
   isliye stack top pop karke current ko bhi skip kar dete hain.
5. Agar stack empty ho gaya ya top negative hai,
   to current negative asteroid safe hai, so push kar do.
6. End me stack me jo bache hain wahi final surviving asteroids hain.

Main idea:
Collision sirf tab hota hai jab left me positive aur current negative ho.
Stack already surviving asteroids ko maintain karta hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] asteroidCollision(int[] asteroids) {

        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = asteroids.length;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            //if positive krdo push kyuki agr pehle se negative vala bhi hua to bhi dikkt nahi kyuki direction opp hai
            if(asteroids[i] > 0){
                stack.push(asteroids[i]);
            }
            //Negative value
            else{
                while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() > 0 && stack.peek() < Math.abs(asteroids[i])){
                    stack.pop();
                }

                if(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() == Math.abs(asteroids[i])){
                    stack.pop();
                }

                else if(stack.isEmpty() || stack.peek() < 0){
                    stack.push(asteroids[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        while(!stack.isEmpty()){
            ans.add(stack.pop());
        }

        Collections.reverse(ans);
        int m = ans.size();
        int[] result = new int[m];
        for(int i=0; i<m; i++){
            result[i] = ans.get(i);
        }

        return result;
        
    }
}
